OB:
The class org.eclipse.swt.internal.BidiUtil in the win32 version has a line as follows:
static Callback callback = new Callback (BidiUtil.class, "windowProc", 4);
The BidiUtil.class uses syntactic sugar for Class.forName("org...BidiUtil"), which is causing a problem. When the method is called, it throws a NoClassDefFoundError, which is not defined in the CLDC class libraries. This issue is only visible when verifying or using jxeLink or similar tools. The Eclipse compiler and Sun's compiler do not produce a compiler error for this.
